  "texts": [
    "The three graph neural networks (GCN, GAT, and GTransformer) use pairwise relations.",
    "While they perform reasonably well, their scores are generally lower than our method.",
    "For instance, GCN achieves an accuracy of 0.7030 for MBTI and 0.8830 for Enneagram, while GAT achieves 0.7347 for MBTI and 0.8959 for Enneagram.",
    "These results highlight the limitation of dyadic graphs in fully capturing the nuanced social interactions.",
    "The large language model (Chatgpt-3.0) performs significantly worse across all metrics, with an accuracy of only 0.0891 for both MBTI and Enneagram traits."
  ],
